  39,1,"The revelation of this Book is from God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  39,2,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth, so worship God ňĻaloneňļ, being sincerely devoted to Him"
  39,3,"Indeed, sincere devotion is due ňĻonlyňļ to God. As for those who take other lords besides Him, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúWe worship them only so they may bring us closer to God,‚ÄĚ surely God will judge between all¬†regarding what they differed about. God certainly does not guide whoever persists in lying and disbelief"
  39,4,"Had it been God‚Äôs Will to have offspring, He could have chosen whatever He willed of His creation. Glory be to Him! He is God‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He wraps the night around the day, and wraps the day around the night. And He has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. He is truly the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you ňĻallňļ from a single soul,¬†then from it He made its mate.¬†And He produced for you four pairs of cattle.¬†He creates you in the wombs of your mothers ňĻin stagesňļ, one development after another, in three layers of darkness.¬†That is God‚ÄĒyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be turned away"
  39,7,"If you disbelieve, then ňĻknow thatňļ God is truly not in need of you, nor does He approve of disbelief from His servants. But if you become grateful ňĻthrough faithňļ, He will appreciate that from you. No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. Then to your Lord is your return, and He will inform you of what you used to do. He certainly knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  39,8,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ňĻaloneňļ. But as soon as He showers them with blessings from Him, they ňĻtotallyňļ forget the One they had cried to earlier, and set up equals to God to mislead ňĻothersňļ from His Way. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúEnjoy your disbelief for a little while! You will certainly be one of the inmates of the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  39,9,"ňĻAre they betterňļ or those who worship ňĻtheir Lordňļ devoutly in the hours of the night, prostrating and standing, fearing the Hereafter and hoping for the mercy of their Lord? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAre those who know equal to those who do not know?‚ÄĚ None will be mindful ňĻof thisňļ except people of reason"
  39,10,"Say ňĻO Prophet, that God saysňļ, ‚ÄúO My servants who believe! Be mindful of your Lord. Those who do good in this world will have a good reward. And God‚Äôs earth is spacious. Only those who endure patiently will be given their reward without limit.‚ÄĚ"
  39,11,"Say, ‚ÄúI am commanded to worship God, being sincerely devoted to Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  39,12,And I am commanded to be the first of those who submit ňĻto His Willňļ.‚ÄĚ
  39,13,"Say, ‚ÄúI truly fear‚ÄĒif I were to disobey my Lord‚ÄĒthe torment of a tremendous Day.‚ÄĚ"
  39,14,"Say, ‚ÄúIt is ňĻonlyňļ God that I worship, being sincere in my devotion to Him"
  39,15,"Worship then whatever ňĻgodsňļ you want instead of Him.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúThe ňĻtrueňļ losers are those who will lose themselves and their families on Judgment Day. That is indeed the clearest loss.‚ÄĚ"
  39,16,"They will have layers of fire above and below them. That is what God warns His servants with. So fear Me, O My servants"
  39,17,"And those who shun the worship of false gods, turning to God ňĻaloneňļ, will have good news. So give good news to My servants ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒ"
  39,18,"those who listen to what is said and follow the best of it.¬†These are the ones ňĻrightlyňļ guided by God, and these are ňĻtrulyňļ the people of reason"
  39,19,What about those against whom the decree of torment has been justified? Is it you ňĻO Prophetňļ who will then save those bound for the Fire
  39,20,"But those mindful of their Lord will have ňĻelevatedňļ mansions, built one above the other, under which rivers flow. ňĻThat isňļ the promise of God. ňĻAndňļ God never fails in ňĻHisňļ promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see that God sends down rain from the sky‚ÄĒchannelling it through streams in the earth‚ÄĒthen produces with it crops of various colours, then they dry up and you see them wither, and then He reduces them to chaff? Surely in this is a reminder for people of reason"
  39,22,"Can ňĻthe misguided be likeňļ those whose hearts God has opened to Islam, so they are enlightened by their Lord? So woe to those whose hearts are hardened at the remembrance of God! It is they who are clearly astray"
  39,23,"ňĻIt isňļ God ňĻWhoňļ has sent down the best message‚ÄĒa Book of perfect consistency and repeated lessons‚ÄĒwhich causes the skin ňĻand heartsňļ of those who fear their Lord to tremble, then their skin and hearts soften at the mention of ňĻthe mercy ofňļ God. That is the guidance of God, through which He guides whoever He wills. But whoever God leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  39,24,"Are those who will only have their ňĻbareňļ faces to shield themselves from the awful torment on Judgment Day ňĻbetter than those in Paradiseňļ? It will ňĻthenňļ be said to the wrongdoers: ‚ÄúReap what you sowed!‚ÄĚ"
  39,25,"Those before them ňĻalsoňļ rejected ňĻthe truthňļ, then the torment came upon them from where they least expected"
  39,26,"So God made them taste humiliation in this worldly life, but far worse is the punishment of the Hereafter, if only they knew"
  39,27,"We have certainly set forth every ňĻkind ofňļ lesson for people in this Quran, so perhaps they will be mindful"
