  41,5,"They say, ‚ÄúOur hearts are veiled against what you are calling us to, there is deafness in our ears, and there is a barrier between us and you. So do ňĻwhatever you wantňļ and so shall we!‚ÄĚ"
  41,6,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI am only a man like you, ňĻbutňļ it has been revealed to me that your God is only One God. So take the Straight Way towards Him, and seek His forgiveness. And woe to the polytheists‚ÄĒ"
  41,7,those who do not pay alms-tax and are in denial of the Hereafter
  41,8,ňĻButňļ those who believe and do good will certainly have a never-ending reward
  41,9,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúHow can you disbelieve in the One Who created the earth in two Days? And how can you set up equals with Him? That is the Lord of all worlds"
  41,10,"He placed on the earth firm mountains, standing high, showered His blessings upon it, and ordained ňĻallňļ its means of sustenance‚ÄĒtotaling four Days exactly‚ÄĒfor all who ask"
  41,11,"Then He turned towards the heaven when it was ňĻstill likeňļ smoke, saying to it and to the earth, ‚ÄėSubmit, willingly or unwillingly.‚Äô They both responded, ‚ÄėWe submit willingly.‚Äô"
  41,12,"So He formed the heaven into seven heavens in two Days, assigning to each its mandate. And We adorned the lowest heaven with ňĻstars likeňļ lamps ňĻfor beautyňļ and for protection. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing.‚ÄĚ"
  41,13,"If they turn away, then say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI warn you of a ňĻmightyňļ blast, like the one that befell ‚Äô»ād and Tham√Ľd.‚ÄĚ"
  41,14,"The messengers had come to them from all angles, ňĻproclaiming,ňļ ‚ÄúWorship none but God.‚ÄĚ They responded, ‚ÄúHad our Lord willed, He could have easily sent down angels ňĻinsteadňļ. So we totally reject what you have been sent with.‚ÄĚ"
  41,15,"As for ‚Äô»ād, they acted arrogantly throughout the land with no right, boasting, ‚ÄúWho is superior to us in might?‚ÄĚ Did they not see that God ňĻHimselfňļ, Who created them, was far superior to them in might? Still they persisted in denying Our signs"
  41,16,"So We sent against them a furious wind,¬†for ňĻseveralňļ miserable days, to make them taste a humiliating punishment in this worldly life. But far more humiliating will be the punishment of the Hereafter. And they will not be helped"
  41,17,"As for Tham√Ľd, We showed them guidance, but they preferred blindness over guidance. So the blast of a disgracing punishment overtook them for what they used to commit"
