  41,24,"Even if they endure patiently, the Fire will ňĻalwaysňļ be their home. And if they ňĻbeg toňļ appease ňĻtheir Lordňļ, they will never be allowed to"
  41,25,"We placed at their disposal ňĻevilňļ associates who made their past and future ňĻmisdeedsňļ appealing to them.¬†ňĻSoňļ the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified against them ňĻas wellňļ, ňĻforňļ they were truly losers"
  41,26,"The disbelievers advised ňĻone anotherňļ, ‚ÄúDo not listen to this Quran but drown it out so that you may prevail.‚ÄĚ"
  41,27,"So We will certainly make the disbelievers taste a severe punishment, and We will surely repay them according to the worst of their deeds"
  41,28,"That is the reward of God‚Äôs enemies: the Fire, which will be their eternal home‚ÄĒa ňĻfittingňļ reward for their denial of Our revelations"
  41,29,"The disbelievers will ňĻthenňļ cry, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Show us those jinn and humans who led us astray: we will put them under our feet so that they will be among the lowest ňĻin Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  41,30,"Surely those who say, ‚ÄúOur Lord is God,‚ÄĚ and then remain steadfast, the angels descend upon them,¬†ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not fear, nor grieve. Rather, rejoice in the good news of Paradise, which you have been promised"
  41,31,"We are your supporters in this worldly life and in the Hereafter. There you will have whatever your souls desire, and there you will have whatever you ask for"
