  45,2,"The revelation of this Book is from God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  45,3,Surely in ňĻthe creation ofňļ the heavens and the earth are signs for the believers
  45,4,"And in your own creation, and whatever living beings He dispersed, are signs for people of sure faith"
  45,5,"And ňĻinňļ the alternation of the day and the night, the provision¬†sent down from the skies by God‚ÄĒreviving the earth after its death‚ÄĒand the shifting of the winds, are signs for people of understanding"
  45,6,These are God‚Äôs revelations which We recite to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth. So what message will they believe in after ňĻdenyingňļ God and His revelations
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"They hear God‚Äôs revelations recited to them, then persist ňĻin denialňļ arrogantly as if they did not hear them. So give them good news of a painful punishment"
  45,9,"And whenever they learn anything of Our revelations, they make a mockery of it. It is they who will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  45,10,"Awaiting them is Hell. Their ňĻworldlyňļ gains will not be of any benefit to them whatsoever, nor will those protectors they have taken besides God. And they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  45,11,This ňĻQuranňļ is ňĻtrueňļ guidance. And those who deny their Lord‚Äôs revelations will suffer the ňĻworstňļ torment of agonizing pain
  45,12,"God is the One Who has subjected the sea for you so that ships may sail upon it by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and that perhaps you will be grateful"
  45,13,He ňĻalsoňļ subjected for you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth‚ÄĒall by His grace. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect
  45,14,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Tell the believers to forgive those who do not fear God‚Äôs days ňĻof tormentňļ, so that He will reward each group for what they used to commit"
  45,15,"Whoever does good, it is to their own benefit. And whoever does evil, it is to their own loss. Then to your Lord you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  45,16,"Indeed, We gave the Children of Israel the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood; granted them good, lawful provisions; and favoured them above the others"
  45,17,We ňĻalsoňļ gave them clear commandments regarding ňĻtheirňļ faith. But it was not until knowledge came to them that they differed out of mutual envy.¬†Surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences
  45,18,"Now We have set you ňĻO Prophetňļ on the ňĻclearňļ Way of faith. So follow it, and do not follow the desires of those who do not know ňĻthe truthňļ"
  45,19,"They certainly can be of no benefit to you against God whatsoever. Surely the wrongdoers are patrons of each other, whereas God is the Patron of the righteous"
  45,20,This ňĻQuranňļ is an insight for humanity‚ÄĒa guide and mercy for people of sure faith
  45,21,Or do those who commit evil deeds ňĻsimplyňļ think that We will make them equal‚ÄĒin their life and after their death‚ÄĒto those who believe and do good? How wrong is their judgment
  45,22,"For God created the heavens and the earth for a purpose, so that every soul may be paid back for what it has committed. And none will be wronged"
  45,23,"Have you seen ňĻO Prophetňļ those who have taken their own desires as their god? ňĻAnd soňļ God left them to stray knowingly, sealed their hearing and hearts, and placed a cover on their sight. Who then can guide them after God? Will you ňĻallňļ not then be mindful"
  45,24,"And they argue, ‚ÄúThere is nothing beyond our worldly life. We die;¬†others are born. And nothing destroys us but ňĻthe passage ofňļ time.‚ÄĚ Yet they have no knowledge ňĻin supportňļ of this ňĻclaimňļ. They only speculate"
  45,25,"And whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, their only argument is to say: ‚ÄúBring our forefathers back, if what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  45,26,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻIt isňļ God ňĻWhoňļ gives you life, then causes you to die, then will gather you ňĻallňļ on the Day of Judgment, about which there is no doubt. But most people do not know.‚ÄĚ"
  45,27,"To God ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. On the Day the Hour will be established, the people of falsehood will then be in ňĻtotalňļ loss"
  45,28,"And you will see every faith-community on its knees. Every community will be summoned to its record ňĻof deedsňļ. ňĻThey all will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúThis Day you will be rewarded for what you used to do"
  45,29,"This record of Ours speaks the truth about you. Indeed, We always had your deeds recorded ňĻby the angelsňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  45,30,"As for those who believed and did good, their Lord will admit them into His mercy. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the absolute triumph"
  45,31,"And as for those who disbelieved, ňĻthey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúWere My revelations not recited to you, yet you acted arrogantly and were a wicked people"
  45,32,"And whenever it was said ňĻto youňļ, ‚ÄėSurely God‚Äôs promise ňĻof judgmentňļ is true and there is no doubt about the Hour,‚Äô you said ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄėWe do not know what the Hour is! We think it is no more than speculation, and we are not convinced ňĻthat it will ever comeňļ.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  45,33,"And the evil ňĻconsequencesňļ of their deeds will unfold before them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  45,34,"It will be said, ‚ÄúThis Day We will neglect you as you neglected the meeting of this Day of yours! Your home will be the Fire, and you will have no helpers"
  45,35,"This is because you made a mockery of God‚Äôs revelations, and were deluded by ňĻyourňļ worldly life.‚ÄĚ So ňĻfromňļ that Day ňĻonňļ they will not be taken out of the Fire, nor will they be allowed to appease ňĻtheir Lordňļ"
  45,36,"So all praise is for God‚ÄĒLord of the heavens and Lord of the earth, Lord of all worlds"
  45,37,"To Him belongs ňĻallňļ Majesty in the heavens and the earth. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,1,Šł§√Ę-Mń©m
  46,2,"The revelation of this Book is from God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,3,We only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet the disbelievers are turning away from what they have been warned about
  46,4,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúHave you considered whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides God? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in ňĻthe creation ofňļ the heavens? Bring me a scripture ňĻrevealedňļ before this ňĻQuranňļ or a shred of knowledge, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  46,5,"And who could be more astray than those who call upon others besides God‚ÄĒňĻothersňļ that cannot respond to them until the Day of Judgment, and are ňĻevenňļ unaware of their calls"
  46,6,"And when ňĻsuchňļ people will be gathered together, those ňĻgodsňļ will be their enemies and will disown their worship"
  46,7,"Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, ‚ÄúThis is pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  46,8,"Or do they say, ‚ÄúHe¬†has fabricated this ňĻQuranňļ!‚ÄĚ? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf I have done so, then there is nothing whatsoever you can do to save me from God. He knows best what ňĻslursňļ you indulge about it. Sufficient is He as a Witness between you and me. And He is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  46,9,"Say, ‚ÄúI am not the first messenger ever sent, nor do I know what will happen to me or you. I only follow what is revealed to me. And I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ"
  46,10,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúConsider if this ňĻQuranňļ is ňĻtrulyňļ from God and you deny it, and a witness from the Children of Israel attests to it and then believes,¬†whereas you act arrogantly. Surely God does not guide the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  46,11,"The disbelievers say of the believers, ‚ÄúHad it been ňĻsomethingňļ good, they¬†would not have beaten us to it.‚ÄĚ Now since they reject its guidance, they will say, ‚ÄúňĻThis isňļ an ancient fabrication!‚ÄĚ"
  46,12,"And before this ňĻQuranňļ the Book of Moses was ňĻrevealed asňļ a guide and mercy. And this Book is a confirmation, in the Arabic tongue, to warn those who do wrong, and as good news to those who do good"
  46,13,"Surely those who say, ‚ÄúOur Lord is God,‚ÄĚ and then remain steadfast‚ÄĒthere will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  46,14,"It is they who will be the residents of Paradise, staying there forever, as a reward for what they used to do"
  46,15,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. Their mothers bore them in hardship and delivered them in hardship. Their ňĻperiod ofňļ bearing and weaning is thirty months. In time, when the child reaches their prime at the age of forty, they pray, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Inspire me to ňĻalwaysňļ be thankful for Your favours which You blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please You. And instil righteousness in my offspring. I truly repent to You, and I truly submit ňĻto Your Willňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  46,16,"It is from these ňĻpeopleňļ that We will accept the good they did, and overlook their misdeeds‚ÄĒalong with the residents of Paradise, ňĻin fulfilment ofňļ the true promise they have been given"
  46,17,"But some scold their parents, ‚ÄúEnough with you! Are you warning me that I will be brought forth ňĻfrom the graveňļ, while many generations had already perished before me ňĻfor goodňļ?‚ÄĚ The parents cry to God for help, ňĻand warn their child,ňļ ‚ÄúPity you. Have faith! Surely God‚Äôs promise is true.‚ÄĚ But the deniers insist, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but ancient fables.‚ÄĚ"
  46,18,"These are the ones against whom the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified, ňĻforňļ they were truly losers"
  46,19,Each ňĻof the two groupsňļ will be ranked according to what they have done so He may fully reward all. And none will be wronged
  46,20,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day ňĻwhenňļ the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire. ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúYou ňĻalreadyňļ exhausted your ňĻshare ofňļ pleasures during your worldly life, and ňĻfullyňļ enjoyed them. So Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for your arrogance throughout the land with no right, and for your rebelliousness.‚ÄĚ"
  46,21,"And remember the brother of ‚Äô»ād, when he warned his people, who inhabited the sand-hills‚ÄĒthere were certainly warners before and after him‚ÄĒňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúWorship none but God. I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous day.‚ÄĚ"
  46,22,"They argued, ‚ÄúHave you come to turn us away from our gods? Bring us then whatever you threaten us with, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  46,23,"He responded, ‚ÄúThe knowledge ňĻof its timeňļ is only with God. I only convey to you what I have been sent with. But I can see that you are a people acting ignorantly.‚ÄĚ"
  46,24,"Then when they saw the torment as a ňĻdenseňļ cloud approaching their valleys, they said ňĻhappilyňļ, ‚ÄúThis is a cloud bringing us rain.‚ÄĚ ňĻBut H√Ľd replied,ňļ ‚ÄúNo, it is what you sought to hasten: a ňĻfierceňļ wind carrying a painful punishment!‚ÄĚ"
  46,25,"It destroyed everything by the command of its Lord, leaving nothing visible except their ruins. This is how We reward the wicked people"
  46,26,"Indeed, We had established them¬†in a way We have not established you ňĻMeccansňļ. And We gave them hearing, sight, and intellect. But neither their hearing, sight, nor intellect were of any benefit to them whatsoever, since they persisted in denying God‚Äôs signs. And ňĻsoňļ they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  46,27,We certainly destroyed the societies around you after having varied the signs so perhaps they would return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ
  46,28,"Why then did those ňĻidolsňļ they took as gods‚ÄĒhoping to get closer ňĻto Himňļ‚ÄĒnot come to their aid? Instead, they failed them. That is ňĻthe result ofňļ their lies and their fabrications"
  46,29,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when We sent a group of jinn your way to listen to the Quran. Then, upon hearing it, they said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúListen quietly!‚ÄĚ Then when it was over, they returned to their fellow jinn as warners"
  46,30,"They declared, ‚ÄúO our fellow jinn! We have truly heard a scripture revealed after Moses, confirming what came before it. It guides to the truth and the Straight Way"
  46,31,"O our fellow jinn! Respond to the caller of God and believe in him, He will forgive your sins and protect you from a painful punishment"
  46,32,"And whoever does not respond to the caller of God will have no escape on earth, nor will they have any protectors against Him. It is they who are clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  46,33,"Do they not realize that God, Who created the heavens and the earth and did not tire in creating them,¬†is able to give life to the dead? Yes ňĻindeedňļ! He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  46,34,"And on the Day the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire, ňĻthey will be asked,ňļ ‚ÄúIs this ňĻHereafterňļ not the truth?‚ÄĚ They will cry, ‚ÄúAbsolutely, by our Lord!‚ÄĚ It will be said, ‚ÄúThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  46,35,"So endure patiently, as did the Messengers of Firm Resolve.¬†And do not ňĻseek toňļ hasten ňĻthe tormentňļ for the deniers. On the Day they see what they have been threatened with, it will be as if they had only stayed ňĻin this worldňļ for an hour of a day.¬†ňĻThis isňļ a ňĻsufficientňļ warning! Then, will anyone be destroyed except the rebellious people"
  47,1,"Those who disbelieve and hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of God, He will render their deeds void"
  47,2,"As for those who believe, do good, and have faith in what has been revealed to MuŠł•ammad‚ÄĒwhich is the truth from their Lord‚ÄĒHe will absolve them of their sins and improve their condition"
  47,3,"This is because the disbelievers follow falsehood, while the believers follow the truth from their Lord. This is how God shows people their true state ňĻof faithňļ"
  47,4,"So when you meet the disbelievers ňĻin battleňļ, strike ňĻtheirňļ necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later ňĻfree them either asňļ an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had God willed, He ňĻHimselfňļ could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does ňĻthis only toňļ test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of God,¬†He will never render their deeds void"
  47,5,"He will guide them ňĻto their rewardňļ, improve their condition"
  47,6,"and admit them into Paradise, having made it known to them"
  47,7,"O believers! If you stand up for God, He will help you and make your steps firm"
  47,8,"As for the disbelievers, may they be doomed and may He render their deeds void"
  47,9,"That is because they detest what God has revealed, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,10,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those before them? God annihilated them, and a similar fate awaits the disbelievers"
  47,11,This is because God is the Patron of the believers while the disbelievers have no patron
  47,12,"Surely God will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens under which rivers flow. As for the disbelievers, they enjoy themselves and feed like cattle.¬†But the Fire will be their home"
  47,13,"ňĻImagine, O Prophet,ňļ how many societies We destroyed that were far superior in might than your society‚ÄĒwhich drove you out‚ÄĒand there was none to help them"
  47,14,Can those ňĻbelieversňļ who stand on clear proof from their Lord be like those whose evil deeds are made appealing to them and ňĻonlyňļ follow their desires
  47,15,"The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that in it are rivers of fresh water, rivers of milk that never changes in taste, rivers of wine delicious to drink, and rivers of pure honey. There they will ňĻalsoňļ have all kinds of fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. ňĻCan they beňļ like those who will stay in the Fire forever, left to drink boiling water that will tear apart their insides"
  47,16,"There are some of them who listen to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, but when they depart from you, they say ňĻmockinglyňļ to those ňĻbelieversňļ gifted with knowledge, ‚ÄúWhat did he just say?‚ÄĚ These are the ones whose hearts God has sealed and who ňĻonlyňļ follow their desires"
  47,17,"As for those who are ňĻrightlyňļ guided, He increases them in guidance and blesses them with righteousness"
  47,18,"Are they only waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise? Yet ňĻsome ofňļ its signs have already come.¬†Once it actually befalls them, will it not be too late to be mindful"
  47,19,"So, know ňĻwell, O Prophet,ňļ that there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except God. And seek forgiveness for your shortcomings¬†and for ňĻthe sins ofňļ the believing men and women. For God ňĻfullyňļ knows your movements and places of rest ňĻO peopleňļ"
  47,20,"And the believers say, ‚ÄúIf only a s√Ľrah¬†was revealed ňĻallowing self-defenceňļ!‚ÄĚ Yet when a precise s√Ľrah¬†is revealed, in which fighting is ňĻexplicitlyňļ mentioned, you see those with sickness in their hearts staring at you like someone in the throes of death. It would have been better for them"
