  48,3,and so that God will help you tremendously
  48,4,"He is the One Who sent down serenity upon the hearts of the believers so that they may increase even more in their faith. To God ňĻaloneňļ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  48,5,So He may admit believing men and women¬†into Gardens under which rivers flow‚ÄĒto stay there forever‚ÄĒand absolve them of their sins. And that is a supreme achievement in the sight of God
  48,6,"Also ňĻso thatňļ He may punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, who harbour evil thoughts of God.¬†May ill-fate befall them! God is displeased with them. He has condemned them and prepared for them Hell. What an evil destination"
  48,7,"To God ňĻaloneňļ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,8,"Indeed, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ We have sent you as a witness, a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  48,9,"so that you ňĻbelieversňļ may have faith in God and His Messenger, support and honour him, and glorify God morning and evening"
  48,10,"Surely those who pledge allegiance to you ňĻO Prophetňļ are actually pledging allegiance to God. God‚Äôs Hand is over theirs. Whoever breaks their pledge, it will only be to their own loss. And whoever fulfils their pledge to God, He will grant them a great reward"
  48,11,"The nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, will say to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWe were preoccupied with our wealth and families, so ask for forgiveness for us.‚ÄĚ They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, ‚ÄúWho then can stand between you and God in any way, if He intends harm or benefit for you? In fact, God is All-Aware of what you do"
  48,12,"The truth is: you thought that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families again. And that was made appealing in your hearts. You harboured evil thoughts ňĻabout Godňļ, and ňĻsoňļ became a doomed people.‚ÄĚ"
  48,13,"And whoever does not believe in God and His Messenger, then We surely have prepared for the disbelievers a blazing Fire"
  48,14,"To God ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  48,15,"Those who stayed behind will say, when you ňĻbelieversňļ set out to take the spoils of war, ‚ÄúLet us accompany you.‚ÄĚ They wish to change God‚Äôs promise.¬†Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYou will not accompany us. This is what God has said before.‚ÄĚ They will then say, ‚ÄúIn fact, you are driven by jealousy against us!‚ÄĚ¬†The truth is: they can hardly comprehend"
  48,16,"Say to nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, ‚ÄúYou will be called ňĻto fightňļ against a people of great might,¬†who you will fight unless they submit. If you then obey, God will grant you a fine reward. But if you turn away as you did before, He will inflict upon you a painful punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  48,17,"There is no blame on the blind, or the disabled, or the sick ňĻfor staying behindňļ. And whoever obeys God and His Messenger will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow. But whoever turns away will be subjected by Him to a painful punishment"
  48,18,"Indeed, God was pleased with the believers when they pledged allegiance to you ňĻO Prophetňļ under the tree. He knew what was in their hearts, so He sent down serenity upon them and rewarded them with a victory at hand"
