  49,6,"O believers, if an evildoer brings you any news, verify ňĻitňļ so you do not harm people unknowingly, becoming regretful for what you have done"
  49,7,"And keep in mind that God‚Äôs Messenger is ňĻstillňļ in your midst. If he were to yield to you in many matters, you would surely suffer ňĻthe consequencesňļ.¬†But God has endeared faith to you, making it appealing in your hearts. And He has made disbelief, rebelliousness, and disobedience detestable to you. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"ňĻThis isňļ a bounty and a blessing from God. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  49,9,"And if two groups of believers fight each other, then make peace between them. But if one of them transgresses against the other, then fight against the transgressing group until they ňĻare willing toňļ submit to the rule of God. If they do so, then make peace between both ňĻgroupsňļ in all fairness and act justly. Surely God loves those who uphold justice"
  49,10,"The believers are but one brotherhood, so make peace between your brothers. And be mindful of God so you may be shown mercy"
  49,11,"O believers! Do not let some ňĻmenňļ ridicule others, they may be better than them, nor let ňĻsomeňļ women ridicule other women, they may be better than them. Do not defame one another, nor call each other by offensive nicknames. How evil it is to act rebelliously after having faith! And whoever does not repent, it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  49,12,"O believers! Avoid many suspicions, ňĻforňļ indeed, some suspicions are sinful. And do not spy, nor backbite one another. Would any of you like to eat the flesh of their dead brother? You would despise that!¬†And fear God. Surely God is ňĻtheňļ Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  49,13,"O humanity! Indeed, We created you from a male and a female, and made you into peoples and tribes so that you may ňĻget toňļ know one another. Surely the most noble of you in the sight of God is the most righteous among you. God is truly All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  49,14,"ňĻSome ofňļ the nomadic Arabs say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYou have not believed. But say, ‚ÄėWe have submitted,‚Äô for faith has not yet entered your hearts.¬†But if you obey God and His Messenger ňĻwholeheartedlyňļ, He will not discount anything from ňĻthe reward ofňļ your deeds. God is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  49,15,The ňĻtrueňļ believers are only those who believe in God and His Messenger‚ÄĒnever doubting‚ÄĒand strive with their wealth and their lives in the cause of God. They are the ones true in faith
  49,16,"Say, ‚ÄúDo you inform God of your faith, when God ňĻalreadyňļ knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things.‚ÄĚ"
