  72,1,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIt has been revealed to me that a group of jinn listened ňĻto the Quran,ňļ and said ňĻto their fellow jinnňļ: ‚ÄėIndeed, we have heard a wondrous recitation"
  72,2,"It leads to Right Guidance so we believed in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord ňĻin worshipňļ"
  72,3,"ňĻNow, we believe thatňļ our Lord‚ÄĒExalted is His Majesty‚ÄĒhas neither taken a mate nor offspring"
  72,4,and that the foolish of us used to utter ňĻoutrageousňļ falsehoods about God
  72,5,We certainly thought that humans and jinn would never speak lies about God
  72,6,And some men used to seek refuge with some jinn‚ÄĒso they increased each other in wickedness
  72,7,"And those ňĻhumansňļ thought, just like you ňĻjinnňļ, that God would not resurrect anyone ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  72,8,"ňĻEarlierňļ we tried to reach heaven ňĻfor newsňļ, only to find it filled with stern guards and shooting stars"
  72,9,"We used to take up positions there for eavesdropping, but whoever dares eavesdrop now will find a flare¬†lying in wait for them"
  72,10,"Now, we have no clue whether evil is intended for those on earth, or their Lord intends for them what is right"
  72,11,Among us are those who are righteous and those who are less so. We have been of different factions
  72,12,"ňĻNow,ňļ we truly know that we cannot frustrate God on earth, nor can we escape from Him ňĻinto heavenňļ"
  72,13,"When we heard the guidance ňĻof the Quranňļ, we ňĻreadilyňļ believed in it. For whoever believes in their Lord will have no fear of being denied ňĻa rewardňļ or wronged"
  72,14,"And among us are those who have submitted ňĻto Godňļ and those who are deviant. So ňĻas forňļ those who submitted, it is they who have attained Right Guidance"
  72,15,"And as for the deviant, they will be fuel for Hell.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  72,16,"Had the deniers followed the Right Way, We would have certainly granted them abundant rain to drink‚ÄĒ"
